item.dc:creator: @A_New_LIght A New LIght
item.description:
@A_New_LIght wrote:

You did not manifest correctly. The error is stating that it cannot find the client.class file. If you have your java/class files in two separate folders make sure to manifest to the class folder specifically as the batch is going to read the class files.

item.dc:creator: @Josh9 -Josh
item.description:
@Josh9 wrote:

[quote=“wboar, post:4, topic:368559”]In page editor you should see a button called “HTML”. Open it and coppy there this:

[code]

YOUR CLIENT

NOTE:

[/code]

Then Click on Publish button, Then there should come up a window “Published! Now what?”
Just click there --> Publish all pages. Then it should redict you to “Site manager” page.
There you should see a button called “File manager” click on it. Then click on “Single File Uploader” and upload your webclient there (client.jar).
Now your webclient should work. :D[/quote]

I used this guide you have set up for us, and used it step by step. I jarred correctly so thats not the problem, but anyways i get these errors:
